com.cyberfront.crdt

Class GenericCRDTManager<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyberfront.crdt.CRDTManager
      • com.cyberfront.crdt.GenericCRDTManager<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The generic type to manage. The type will need to be annotated to support Jackson serializing as a JSON object. See com.cyberfront.crdt.unittest.data.AbstractDataType for an example of this annotation. Also, the type T should have a constructor which accepts no arguments.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GenericManager, SimCRDTManager

    public class GenericCRDTManager<T>
extends CRDTManager
    The Class GenericCRDTManager is used to manage a Plain Old Java Object (POJO). Internally changes are represented as a series of JSON operations but to the external interface, the object type being managed is given by the generic parameter T
